			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2020</a> paper:</span><br><i>A Precedence-Driven Approach for Concurrent Model Synchronization Scenarios using Triple Graph Grammars</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/LarsFritsche.html">Lars Fritsche</a>, <a href="../profile/JensKosiol.html">Jens Kosiol</a>, <a href="../profile/AdrianMöller.html">Adrian Möller</a>, <a href="../profile/AndySchürr.html">Andy Schürr</a>, <a href="../profile/GabrieleTaentzer.html">Gabriele Taentzer</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3426425.3426931">10.1145/3426425.3426931</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3b.html"><span class="tagM">T3B: Transformation Languages</span></a><ul><li> The paper’s central topic is specifying or applying transformations (rewriting/mapping/synchronization).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It includes substantial tool support or infrastructure relevant for engineering/using languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagL">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It relies on formal methods (definitions/proofs/semantic properties) beyond informal description.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It performs mapping/conversion/synchronization between representations (horizontal transformations).
</li></ul></li></ul>
